      "content": "No, you absolutely should not take Benadryl or any other medication on your own to self-treat chest heaviness, as it could mask a life-threatening heart attack or worsen your condition. Since you have a history of anxiety, the fear of hospital visits is understandable, but the immediate safety risk of ignoring these physical symptoms is far greater than the temporary spike in anxiety from the wait. Please call emergency services right now so they can assess your safety without forcing you into a doctor's office immediately.",
